---

# BRANCH STRATEGY (confirmed by Vova 2026-06-03)

**`dev` IS the V2 base.** The foundation (PR#1533) is already merged into `dev`.
No separate `v2` integration branch. Everything integrates into `dev` step by step.

## Branch-base decision pattern (apply before every task)

One question: **what does this task depend on?**

```
Task depends on nothing in-review?
  → cut from dev  (foundation #1533 already there)

Task needs components/pages from the diagrams redesign (PR#1537)?
  → cut from feat/ct-1527-diagrams-brand-redesign
     PR targets #1537, auto-retargets to dev when #1537 merges

Task needs components/pages from the brand hub redesign (PR#1543)?
  → cut from feat/ct-1529-brand-hub-v2
     PR targets #1543, auto-retargets to dev when #1543 merges
```

**Why branch off in-review instead of waiting?**
If you wait for the base PR to merge you lose a day. Branching off the working branch
gives you the files now. When the base PR merges to dev, your branch auto-integrates —
no big merge at the end, everything flows into dev step by step.

**All PRs ultimately target `dev`.** Stacked PRs auto-retarget when their base merges.

---

# PR MERGE CHAIN

```
Dev (@pedchenkooleh-coo / @DaniilDerkach) opens PR on branch cut from dev (or working branch above)
  → @denistka: runs locally + verifies acceptance criteria
    → @denistka comments "Local test: PASS — {details}"  ← @appdev-v merge signal
      → @appdev-v: final UI/UX + code review
        → @appdev-v merges to dev → deploy crop-dev.app → smoke → prod
```

**Denis's PASS comment is the gate.** Vova does not merge without it.
**Never approve without running locally.** CI green ≠ local test done.

---

# STACKED PR PATTERN (Vova's build style)

Vova ships V2 brand-page work in layers:

1. **Foundation PR** (e.g. front#1533) — shared component library, purely additive, zero page consumers.
   CI: all checks green before review. Review: Denis + Oleg approve → Vova merges to `dev`.

2. **Feature PRs stacked on working branch** (e.g. front#1537 on foundation branch; front#1543).
   CI: only Socket / Vercel / soft-404 run on a stacked PR — this is expected and not a concern.
   Full CI suite triggers automatically when the base branch merges and this PR auto-retargets to `dev`.

**Trigger pattern:** Vova posts in the team channel:
  "Denis + Oleg: [PR links], first one landing unblocks Oleg's [task]."
→ Act immediately. Stacked PRs create a dependency chain; every hour of delay blocks downstream work.

---

# DENIS'S LOCAL REVIEW CHECKLIST

## Step 0 — `.env.local` (before `bun run dev`)
```
SEARCH_API_URL_HONO="https://search-hono-dev-222426967009.us-east1.run.app"
```
Dev hono only — V2 brand diagrams (FRR/VNT/MCH/MAR) and Marcrest catalog data live on
`search-hono-dev`, not prod `search-hono`. Wrong URL → empty diagrams / 404 brands on localhost.

## Step 1 — Checkout
```bash
gh pr checkout {N}
bun install          # only if package.json or bun.lock changed
```

## Step 2 — Typecheck
```bash
bun run type-check   # must be clean, zero errors
```

## Step 3 — Run tests for changed files
```bash
bunx vitest run {changed-paths-from-pr-diff}
# Example: bunx vitest run features/brands/ hooks/use-scroll-spy.test.ts
```

## Step 4 — Read the diff of key files
```bash
git diff origin/{base} -- {key-file}
```
Focus on:
- `page.tsx` changes — breadcrumb hrefs, model link hrefs, Suspense fallbacks, loading.tsx match
- Navigation files — any link that could create a loop (see INVARIANTS.md §F6)
- `brand-registry.ts` / `manufacturer-config.ts` — `available`, `seoIndexed` flags

## Step 5 — Manual style check (CI doesn't catch these)
```bash
grep -n "bg-white\|transition-colors\|ring-2" {changed-components}
grep -rn "#[0-9]\{4\}" {changed-files}   # issue refs in JSDoc
```
Flag each with file:line. Non-blocking on purely additive PRs; must be fixed before live wiring.

## Step 6 — Comment on PR
```
Local test: PASS — {N} tests green, type-check clean, {specific things verified}.

{Optional: style follow-up before wiring to pages (non-blocking):}
bg-white hardcoded → bg-background: file.tsx:NN
transition-colors → transition-all: file.tsx:NN
v3 focus ring (ring-2) → v4 (ring-[3px] ring-ring/50): file.tsx:NN
Issue refs in JSDoc (#NNNN) → strip: file.ts:NN
```

```
Local test: FAIL — {specific thing broken + steps to reproduce}
```

## Step 7 — Approve
```bash
gh pr review {N} --repo CT-CROP/{repo} --approve --body "LGTM — {one line}."
```

---

# WHAT EACH PR TYPE NEEDS

## Purely additive (no page consumers yet)
- typecheck + vitest green
- Storybook stories present for new components
- Style violations noted as non-blocking follow-up

## Page-changing PRs (page.tsx, routing, nav)
- Walk the full path manually in dev browser at 375px + 1280px
- Check breadcrumb hrefs — no loops, correct brand-specific paths
- `loading.tsx` skeleton matches real page layout (prevents CLS / flash)
- `<meta name="robots">` correct on brand pages (`noindex,follow`)
- No JS console errors

## Search/hono PRs
- `bun run test` + `bun run typecheck` (both required)
- `GET /api/brand/{slug}/models` returns 200 or clean 404 (never 500)
- Brand display names: `getBrandDisplayName("FRR"|"VNT"|"MCH"|"MAR")` never returns "UNK"
- `brand-extractor.ts` / `brand-safety.ts` scope unchanged (CNH family only)

## Test-infra / harness PRs (renderWithProviders, mocks, MSW)
- Load `crop-front/TEST_INFRA_RULES.ti` — five structural rules from @appdev-v review (#1939/#1941)
- Colocate moved modules + pin-tests; one canonical home (`test-utils/`); move vs rewrite split
- Spikes → issue comment only; MSW lands with first real `fetchImpl` consumer (#1915)

