# LOCAL-RUN & CI GOTCHAS (learned in practice — not V2-specific)

These bit us during real PR reviews. Check them before concluding a PR is broken.

## 1. `bun install` on EVERY fresh PR-branch checkout
A new branch may carry a different lockfile. Skipping install yields phantom
`Cannot find package 'hono'/'zod'` failures that look like 30+ broken tests but
are just missing deps. Hit on search-hono#332 (31 fake fails → all green after install).
→ After `gh pr checkout N`: run `bun install` before tests, always.

## 2. Stacked-branch checkout collisions
Switching between stacked branches, untracked files from branch A block
`gh pr checkout B` ("untracked working tree files would be overwritten"). And a
local copy of a working branch can diverge with stale base commits.
→ Clean leaked untracked files first; if the local branch diverged from a
  rebased remote, `git reset --hard origin/<branch>` to match origin exactly.

## 3. CI upstream cascade — don't read as multiple bugs
`lint-and-build` fails with "Upstream jobs not successful: security=failure"
when `security` / `Semgrep OSS` fail. It is ONE root cause cascading, not three
independent failures. Fix the upstream (Semgrep finding) and the rest clear.

## 4. Vercel preview gating is an ACCOUNT issue, not code
"Git author <login> must have access to the project on Vercel" = the PR author's
GitHub account lacks Vercel project access. Infra/permissions, not a code defect —
route to Vova, don't try to fix in the diff.

## 5. Commit-msg ≤ 100 chars + commitlint + no-AI hook
CROP-front `.husky/commit-msg` rejects > 100 chars, the word "claude" (any case),
`Co-Authored-By:`, and emoji. (Already in CROP-front/CLAUDE.md — see there for the
full pre-commit chain: ds:validate → cyrillic → emoji → gitleaks → lint-staged.)

